        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "The getModuleDirectory function returns unexpected results when using a more complex directory layout. \r\n\r\n{noformat}\r\napplication\r\n  -\\modules\r\n      -\\mymodule\r\n          -\\controllers\r\n             -\\backend\r\n             -\\frontend\r\n{noformat}\r\n\r\nThe application ini file contains the module directory contains the entry \"resources.frontController.moduleDirectory\" in which the directory is containing the modules is defined so this should be used.\r\n\r\nCurrent result in of the getModuleDirectory function: \/my\/applicatio\/modules\/mymodule\/controllers\r\nExpected result: \/my\/application\/modules\/mymodule\r\n"
